==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: aquifer
<hw>aquifer</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an underground bed or
layer yielding ground water for wells and springs etc.; <as>as, the
Oglala <ex>aquifer</ex></as>. The water contained in an aquifer may be
of great age, and in such cases is sometimes called <col><b>fossil
water</b></col>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aquiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
